title: 'Wake up Zuck!' Protesters gather outside of Facebook CEO's San Francisco home
text: The social network is under fire for allowing politicians to lie in ads.

title: EU industry chief says Facebook needs to adapt to the EU's standards
text: EU industry commissioner Thierry Breton said on Monday that Facebook must adapt to Europe's standards, not the other way around.

title: Facebook pushes EU for dilute and fuzzy Internet content rules
text: Facebook founder Mark Zuckerberg is in Europe this week — attending a security conference in Germany over the weekend where he spoke about the kind of regulation he’d like applied to his platform ahead of a slate of planned meetings with digital heavyweights at the European Commission.

title: Facebook's Zuckerberg meets EU's competition chief ahead of new A.I. rules
text: The European Commission, the EU's executive arm, is due to unveil new regulations on artificial intelligence (AI) Wednesday.

title: Facebook warns of risks to innovation, freedom of expression ahead of EU rules
text: Facebook warned of threats to innovation and freedom of expression on Monday, ahead of the release of a raft of rules by the European Union this week and in coming months to rein in U.S. tech giants and Chinese companies.

title: Mark Zuckerberg comes to Europe and asks for more regulation
text: Mark Zuckerberg has asked for more regulation of Big Tech companies. Europe is preparing to give him what he wants.

title: Facebook's Zuckerberg meeting EU officials ahead of new antitrust rules
text: CNBC's Silvia Amaro outlines what to expect from Mark Zuckerberg's meetings with EU officials in Brussels this week.

title: Facebook CEO Zuckerberg Meets EU Officials in Brussels
text: Facebook Inc. Chief Executive Officer Mark Zuckerberg is in Brussels today to meet with senior officials to discuss new rules and regulations for the internet, two days before the the bloc unveils its plans to legislate artificial intelligence. Maria Tadeo reports on "Bloomberg Surveillance."
